My meme

My meme is about coding everyday and the pain of finding errors that you cant make sense of. It was done through combining multiple images from the internet and adding my own caption.

library(magick)
library(magrittr)

#importing both images by copiyng their addresses 
# scaling the images to fit side by side
kimk1 <- image_read("https://www.the-sun.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2022/04/Screenshot-2022-04-14-08.26.20.png") %>% 
  image_scale(geometry = 215) 

kimk2 <- image_read("http://cdn.thehollywoodgossip.com/uploads/2018/06/kim-kardashian-cries-over-robbery.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(geometry = 237) 

# adding blank image, with color black and adjust width and length to fit the photos
# added a black image using image_blank() and annotating it with the meme text
typed_message <- image_blank(color = "black", height = 50, width = 452) %>%
  image_annotate("When you do four coding papers and you get your millionth\n error message today :)", size = 15, color = "white", gravity = "center")

#combining both photos of Kim Kardashian in collagefinal and append the meme text
collagefinal <- image_append(c(kimk1, kimk2), stack = FALSE)
photowithtext <- image_append(c(collagefinal,typed_message), stack= TRUE)

# save the image as my_meme.jpg
image_write(photowithtext, "my_meme.jpg")

My animated GIF

My animated GIF is about Taylor Swift through her musical career. I was inspired to do this since I am a Taylor Swift fan.

I have include some of my favorite albums - the order they appear in the GIF is:

  1. Speak Now
  2. Reputation
  3. Evermore

library (magick)

# I grabbed different images of taylor swift to create a gif based on her different albums

speaknow <- image_read("https://taylorswiftswitzerland.ch/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/dear-john-taylor-swift-2011.png") %>%
  image_scale(300)

reputation <- image_read("https://hips.hearstapps.com/digitalspyuk.cdnds.net/17/50/1513521903-taylor-swift.jpg?crop=1xw:0.6691428571428572xh;center,top&resize=1200:*") %>%
  image_scale(300)

readyforit <- image_read("https://pyxis.nymag.com/v1/imgs/9a1/947/75f9996f73eff58911a1a44bc6b59db52c-taylor-stare.1x.rsquare.w1400.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)

folklore <- image_read("https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2021/01/02/PFSU/b4062ac1-7164-4b69-a79a-3cc23b09c15d-10taylor-item2-jumbo.jpg?width=1200&disable=upscale&format=pjpg&auto=webp") %>%
  image_scale(300)

# combining all the photos in one variable called animation and turning it into a GIF and setting it to one frame per second
animation <- c(speaknow, reputation, readyforit, folklore) %>%
  image_animate(fps=1)

# it creates a GIF 
image_write(animation, "animated.gif")
